Bahrain-Based AAOIFI Says It May Issue 35 Shariah Rules in 2012

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-09-07T11:27:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/bahrain-based-aaoifi-says-it-may-issue-35-shariah-rules-in-2012.html
The  Accounting & Auditing
Organization for Islamic Financial Institutions , known as
AAOIFI, said it may issue 35 Shariah standards for Islamic
institutions in 2012.  The Bahrain-based organization “conducted in-depth
research for Shariah and auditing standards and guidelines,
which are expected to be finalized next year,” according to an
e-mailed statement citing its secretary general, Mohammed Nedal Alchaar.  AAOIFI, which has more than 200 members from 45 countries,
sets standards that are used in Bahrain, the Dubai International
Financial Centre, Jordan, Lebanon, Qatar,  Sudan  and  Syria ,
according to its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
